{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The old story about climate protection is that it's costly,"},{"time":5000,"text":"or it would have been done already."},{"time":7000,"text":"So government needs to make us do something painful to fix it."},{"time":10000,"text":"The new story about climate protection"},{"time":12000,"text":"is that it's not costly, but profitable."},{"time":14000,"text":"This was a simple sign error,"},{"time":16000,"text":"because it's cheaper to save fuel than to buy fuel,"},{"time":19000,"text":"as is well known to companies that do it all the time --"},{"time":23000,"text":"for example, Dupont, SD micro electronics."},{"time":26000,"text":"Many other firms -- IBM -- are reducing their energy intensity"},{"time":31000,"text":"routinely six percent a year by fixing up their plants,"},{"time":33000,"text":"and they get their money back in two or three years."},{"time":36000,"text":"That's called a profit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"Now, similarly, the old story about oil is that if we wanted to save very much of it,"},{"time":44000,"text":"it would be expensive, or we would have done it already,"},{"time":48000,"text":"because markets are essentially perfect."},{"time":50000,"text":"If, of course, that were true, there would be no innovation,"},{"time":53000,"text":"and nobody could make any money."},{"time":55000,"text":"But the new story about oil"},{"time":57000,"text":"is the government doesn't have to force us to do painful things to get off oil --"},{"time":61000,"text":"not just incrementally, but completely --"},{"time":63000,"text":"quite the contrary. The United States, for example,"},{"time":67000,"text":"can completely eliminate its use of oil"},{"time":70000,"text":"and rejuvenate the economy at the same time,"},{"time":73000,"text":"led by business for profit,"},{"time":75000,"text":"because it's so much cheaper to save and substitute for the oil"},{"time":78000,"text":"than to keep on buying it."},{"time":80000,"text":"This process will also be catalyzed by the military"},{"time":83000,"text":"for its own reasons of combat effectiveness and preventing conflict,"},{"time":87000,"text":"particularly over oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"This thesis is set out in a book called \"Winning the Oil Endgame\""},{"time":94000,"text":"that four colleagues and I wrote"},{"time":96000,"text":"and have posted for free at Oilendgame.com --"},{"time":100000,"text":"about 170,000 downloads so far."},{"time":103000,"text":"And it was co-sponsored by the Pentagon --"},{"time":105000,"text":"it's independent, it's peer-reviewed"},{"time":107000,"text":"and all of the backup calculations are transparently posted for your perusal."},{"time":112000,"text":"Now, a bit of economic history, I think, may be helpful here."},{"time":117000,"text":"Around 1850, one of the biggest U.S. industries was whaling."},{"time":120000,"text":"And whale oil lit practically every building."},{"time":123000,"text":"But in the nine years before Drake struck oil, in 1859,"},{"time":126000,"text":"at least five-sixths of that whale oil-illuminating market disappeared,"},{"time":130000,"text":"thanks to fatal competitors, chiefly oil and gas made from coal,"},{"time":136000,"text":"to which the whalers had not been paying attention."},{"time":139000,"text":"So, very unexpectedly, they ran out of customers"},{"time":143000,"text":"before they ran out of whales."},{"time":145000,"text":"The remnant whale populations were saved by technological innovators"},{"time":149000,"text":"and profit-maximizing capitalists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"And it's funny -- it feels a bit like this now for oil."},{"time":157000,"text":"We've been spending the last few decades"},{"time":159000,"text":"accumulating a very powerful backlog of technologies"},{"time":162000,"text":"for saving and substituting for oil,"},{"time":164000,"text":"and no one had bothered to add them up before."},{"time":167000,"text":"So when we did, we found some very surprising things."},{"time":170000,"text":"Now, there are two big reasons to be concerned about oil."},{"time":174000,"text":"Both national competitiveness and national security are at risk."},{"time":178000,"text":"On the competitiveness front,"},{"time":180000,"text":"we all know that Toyota has more market cap than the big three put together."},{"time":185000,"text":"And serious competition from Europe, from Korea,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and next is China, which will soon be a major net exporter of cars."},{"time":193000,"text":"How long do you think it will take before you can drive home your new"},{"time":196000,"text":"wally-badged Shanghai automotive super-efficient car?"},{"time":202000,"text":"Maybe a decade, according to my friends in Detroit."},{"time":205000,"text":"China has an energy policy"},{"time":207000,"text":"based on radical energy efficiency and leap-frog technology."},{"time":210000,"text":"They're not going to export your uncle's Buick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"And after that comes India."},{"time":215000,"text":"The point here is, these cars are going to be made super efficient."},{"time":219000,"text":"The question is, who will make them?"},{"time":221000,"text":"Will we in the United States continue to import efficient cars to replace foreign oil,"},{"time":226000,"text":"or will we make efficient cars and import neither the oil nor the cars?"},{"time":230000,"text":"That seems to make more sense."},{"time":232000,"text":"The more we keep on using the oil, particularly the imported oil,"},{"time":238000,"text":"the more we face a very obvious array of problems."},{"time":241000,"text":"Our analysis assumes that they all cost nothing,"},{"time":243000,"text":"but nothing is not the right number."},{"time":245000,"text":"It could well be enough to double the oil price, for example."},{"time":249000,"text":"And one of the worst of these"},{"time":251000,"text":"is what it does to our standing in the world"},{"time":254000,"text":"if other countries think that everything we do is about oil,"},{"time":258000,"text":"if we have to treat countries that have oil"},{"time":260000,"text":"differently than countries that don't have oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"And our military get quite unhappy"},{"time":267000,"text":"with having to stand guard on pipelines in Far-off-istan"},{"time":270000,"text":"when what they actually signed up for"},{"time":272000,"text":"was to protect American citizens."},{"time":274000,"text":"They don't like fighting over oil,"},{"time":276000,"text":"they don't like being in the sands"},{"time":278000,"text":"and they don't like where the oil money goes"},{"time":280000,"text":"and what sort of instability it creates."},{"time":282000,"text":"Now, in order to avoid these problems,"},{"time":284000,"text":"whatever you think they're worth, it's actually not that complicated."},{"time":287000,"text":"We can save half the oil by using it more efficiently,"},{"time":290000,"text":"at a cost of 12 dollars per saved barrel."},{"time":294000,"text":"And then we can replace the other half"},{"time":297000,"text":"with a combination of advanced bio-fuels and safe natural gas."},{"time":301000,"text":"And that costs on average under 18 dollars a barrel."},{"time":303000,"text":"And compared with the official forecast,"},{"time":306000,"text":"that oil will cost 26 dollars a barrel in 2025,"},{"time":309000,"text":"which is half of what we've been paying lately,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"that will save 70 billion dollars a year, starting quite soon."},{"time":316000,"text":"Now, in order to do this we need to invest about 180 billion dollars:"},{"time":321000,"text":"half of it to retool the car, truck and plane industries;"},{"time":324000,"text":"half of it to build the advanced bio-fuel industry."},{"time":326000,"text":"In the process, we will gain about a million good jobs, mainly rural."},{"time":332000,"text":"And protect another million jobs now at risk, mainly in auto-making."},{"time":336000,"text":"And we'll also get returns over 150 billion dollars a year."},{"time":340000,"text":"So that's a very handsome return."},{"time":342000,"text":"It's financeable in the private capital market."},{"time":345000,"text":"But if you want it for the reasons I just mentioned,"},{"time":347000,"text":"to happen sooner and with higher confidence,"},{"time":351000,"text":"then -- and also to expand choice and manage risk --"},{"time":355000,"text":"then you might like some light-handed public policies"},{"time":358000,"text":"that support rather than distorting or opposing the business logic."},{"time":363000,"text":"And these policies work fine without taxes, subsidies or mandates."},{"time":368000,"text":"They make a little net money for the treasury."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370000,"text":"They have a broad trans-ideological appeal,"},{"time":372000,"text":"and because we want them actually to happen,"},{"time":374000,"text":"we figured out ways to do them"},{"time":377000,"text":"that do not require much, if any, federal legislation,"},{"time":383000,"text":"and can, indeed, be done administratively or at a state level."},{"time":387000,"text":"Just to illustrate what to do about the nub of the problem,"},{"time":391000,"text":"namely, light vehicles,"},{"time":393000,"text":"here are four ultra-light carbon-composite concept cars with low drag,"},{"time":398000,"text":"and all but the one at the upper left have hybrid drive."},{"time":402000,"text":"You can sort of have it all with these things."},{"time":404000,"text":"For example, this Opel two-seater"},{"time":407000,"text":"does 155 miles an hour at 94 miles a gallon."},{"time":411000,"text":"This muscle car from Toyota: 408 horsepower in an ultra-light"},{"time":416000,"text":"that does zero to 60 in well under four seconds,"},{"time":418000,"text":"and still gets 32 miles a gallon. I'll say more later about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"And in the upper left, a pioneering effort 14 years ago by GM --"},{"time":428000,"text":"84 miles a gallon without even using a hybrid, in a four-seater."},{"time":431000,"text":"Well, saving that fuel, 69 percent of the fuel in light vehicles"},{"time":435000,"text":"costs about 57 cents per saved gallon."},{"time":438000,"text":"But it's even a better deal for heavy trucks,"},{"time":440000,"text":"where you save a similar amount at 25 cents a gallon,"},{"time":444000,"text":"with better aerodynamics and tires and engines, and so on,"},{"time":447000,"text":"and taking out weight so you can put it into payload."},{"time":450000,"text":"So you can double efficiency with a 60 percent internal rate of return."},{"time":455000,"text":"Then you can go even further, almost tripling efficiency"},{"time":459000,"text":"with some operational improvements,"},{"time":461000,"text":"double the big haulers' margins."},{"time":463000,"text":"And we intend to use those numbers to create demand pull, and flip the market."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"In the airplane business, it's again a similar story"},{"time":472000,"text":"where the first 20 percent fuel saving is free,"},{"time":475000,"text":"as Boeing is now demonstrating in its new Dreamliner."},{"time":478000,"text":"But then the next generation of planes saves about half."},{"time":482000,"text":"Again, much cheaper than buying the fuel."},{"time":485000,"text":"And if you go over the next 15 years or so to a blended-wing body,"},{"time":489000,"text":"kind of a flying wing with internal engines,"},{"time":493000,"text":"then you get about a factor three efficiency improvement"},{"time":497000,"text":"at comparable or lower cost."},{"time":499000,"text":"Let me focus a minute on the light vehicles, the cars and light trucks,"},{"time":503000,"text":"because we all know the most about those;"},{"time":505000,"text":"probably everybody here drives one."},{"time":508000,"text":"And yet we may not realize that in a standard sedan,"},{"time":511000,"text":"of all the fuel energy you feed into the car,"},{"time":514000,"text":"seven-eighths never gets to the wheels;"},{"time":516000,"text":"it's lost first in the engine, idling at zero miles a gallon,"},{"time":520000,"text":"the power train and accessories."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"So then of the energy that does get to the wheels,"},{"time":526000,"text":"only an eighth of it, half of that, goes to heat the tires on the road,"},{"time":529000,"text":"or to heat the air the car pushes aside."},{"time":531000,"text":"And only this little bit, only six percent"},{"time":533000,"text":"actually ends up accelerating the car"},{"time":536000,"text":"and then heating the brakes when you stop."},{"time":538000,"text":"In fact, since 95 percent of the weight you're moving is the car not the driver,"},{"time":541000,"text":"less than one percent of the fuel energy ends up moving the driver."},{"time":544000,"text":"This is not very gratifying"},{"time":546000,"text":"after more than a century of devoted engineering effort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":551000,"text":"Moreover, three-fourths of the fuel use is caused by the weight of the car."},{"time":557000,"text":"And it's obvious from the diagram that every unit of energy you save at the wheels"},{"time":562000,"text":"is going to avoid wasting another seven units of energy"},{"time":565000,"text":"getting that energy to the wheels."},{"time":567000,"text":"So there's huge leverage for making the car a lot lighter."},{"time":571000,"text":"And the reason this has not been very seriously examined before"},{"time":574000,"text":"is there was a common assumption in the industry that --"},{"time":578000,"text":"well, then it might not be safe if you got whacked by a heavy car,"},{"time":581000,"text":"and it would cost a lot more to make,"},{"time":583000,"text":"because the only way we know how to make cars much lighter"},{"time":585000,"text":"was to use expensive light metals like aluminum and magnesium."},{"time":589000,"text":"But these objections are now vanishing through advances in materials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593000,"text":"For example, we use a lot of carbon-fiber composites"},{"time":597000,"text":"in sporting goods."},{"time":599000,"text":"And it turns out that these are quite remarkable for safety."},{"time":604000,"text":"Here's a handmade McLaren SLR carbon car that got t-boned by a Golf."},{"time":609000,"text":"The Golf was totaled."},{"time":611000,"text":"The McLaren just popped off and scratched the side panel."},{"time":614000,"text":"They'll pop it back on and fix the scratch later."},{"time":617000,"text":"But if this McLaren were to run into a wall at 65 miles an hour,"},{"time":620000,"text":"the entire crash energy would be absorbed"},{"time":623000,"text":"by a couple of woven carbon-fiber composite cones,"},{"time":626000,"text":"weighing a total of 15 pounds, hidden in the front end."},{"time":630000,"text":"Because these materials could actually absorb"},{"time":632000,"text":"six to 12 times as much energy per pound as steel,"},{"time":636000,"text":"and do so a lot more smoothly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"And this means we've just cracked the conundrum of safety and weight."},{"time":643000,"text":"We could make cars bigger, which is protective, but make them light."},{"time":650000,"text":"Whereas if we made them heavy, they'd be both hostile and inefficient."},{"time":654000,"text":"And when you make them light in the right way,"},{"time":656000,"text":"that can be simpler and cheaper to make."},{"time":661000,"text":"You can end up saving money, and lives, and oil, all at the same time."},{"time":666000,"text":"I showed here two years ago"},{"time":668000,"text":"a little bit about a design of your basic, uncompromised,"},{"time":672000,"text":"quintupled-efficiency suburban-assault vehicle --"},{"time":677000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":678000,"text":"-- and this is a complete virtual design"},{"time":683000,"text":"that is production-costed manufacturable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686000,"text":"And the process needed to make it"},{"time":688000,"text":"is actually coming toward the market quite nicely."},{"time":691000,"text":"We figured out a kind of a digital inkjet printer"},{"time":694000,"text":"for this very stiff, strong, carbon-composite material,"},{"time":700000,"text":"and then ways to thermoform it,"},{"time":702000,"text":"because it's a combination of carbon and nylon,"},{"time":705000,"text":"into whatever complex shapes you want,"},{"time":708000,"text":"like the one just shown at the auto show by one of the tier-one suppliers."},{"time":712000,"text":"And the manufacturing you can do this way gets radically simplified."},{"time":716000,"text":"Because the auto body has only, say, 14 parts, instead of 100, 150."},{"time":721000,"text":"Each one is formed by one fairly cheap die set,"},{"time":724000,"text":"instead of four expensive ones for stamping steel."},{"time":727000,"text":"Each of the parts can be easily lifted with no hoist."},{"time":732000,"text":"They snap together like a kid's toy."},{"time":734000,"text":"So you got rid of the body shop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"And if you want, you can lay color in the mold, and get rid of the paint shop."},{"time":739000,"text":"Those are the two hardest and costliest parts of making a car."},{"time":742000,"text":"So you end up with at least two-fifths lower capital intensity"},{"time":745000,"text":"than the leanest plant in the industry, which GM has in Lansing."},{"time":750000,"text":"The plant also gets smaller."},{"time":752000,"text":"Now, when you go through a similar analysis for every way we use oil,"},{"time":756000,"text":"including buildings, industry, feedstocks and so on,"},{"time":759000,"text":"you find that of the 28 million barrels a day"},{"time":762000,"text":"the government says we will need in 2025,"},{"time":765000,"text":"well, about eight of that can be removed by efficiency by then,"},{"time":770000,"text":"with another seven still being saved as the vehicle stocks turn over,"},{"time":774000,"text":"at an average cost of only 12 bucks a barrel,"},{"time":777000,"text":"instead of 26 for buying the oil."},{"time":779000,"text":"And then another six can be made robustly, competitively,"},{"time":784000,"text":"from cellulosic ethanol and a little bio-diesel,"},{"time":787000,"text":"without interfering at all with the water or land needs of crop production."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"There is a huge amount of gas to be saved,"},{"time":794000,"text":"about half the projected gas at about an eighth of its price."},{"time":798000,"text":"And here are some no-brainer substitutions of it, with lots left over."},{"time":802000,"text":"So much, in fact, that after you've handled the domestic oil forecast"},{"time":809000,"text":"from areas already approved,"},{"time":811000,"text":"you have only this little bit left, and let's see how we can meet that,"},{"time":814000,"text":"because there's a pretty flexible menu of ways."},{"time":817000,"text":"We could, of course, buy more efficiency."},{"time":819000,"text":"Maybe you ought to buy efficiency at 26 bucks instead of 12."},{"time":823000,"text":"Or wait to capture the second half of it."},{"time":825000,"text":"Or we could, of course, just get this little bit"},{"time":827000,"text":"by continuing to import some Canadian and Mexican oil,"},{"time":830000,"text":"or the ethanol the Brazilians would love to sell us."},{"time":833000,"text":"But they'll sell it to Japan and China instead,"},{"time":835000,"text":"because we have tariff barriers to protect our corn farmers, and they don't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839000,"text":"Or we could use the saved gas directly to cover all of this balance,"},{"time":844000,"text":"or if we used it as hydrogen, which is more profitable and efficient,"},{"time":847000,"text":"we'd get rid of the domestic oil too."},{"time":849000,"text":"And that doesn't even count, for example,"},{"time":851000,"text":"that available land in the Dakotas can cost effectively"},{"time":854000,"text":"make enough wind power to run every highway vehicle in the country."},{"time":857000,"text":"So we have lots of options."},{"time":859000,"text":"And the choice of menu and timing is quite flexible."},{"time":863000,"text":"Now, to make this happen quicker and with higher confidence,"},{"time":866000,"text":"there is a few ways government could help."},{"time":868000,"text":"For example, fee-bates, a combination of a fee and a rebate"},{"time":873000,"text":"in any size class of vehicle you want,"},{"time":876000,"text":"can increase the price of inefficient vehicles"},{"time":881000,"text":"and correspondingly pay you a rebate for efficient vehicles."},{"time":885000,"text":"You're not paid to change size class."},{"time":887000,"text":"You are paid to pick efficiency within a size class,"},{"time":891000,"text":"in a way equivalent to looking at all fourteen years of life-cycle fuel savings"},{"time":896000,"text":"rather than just the first two or three."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898000,"text":"This expands choice rapidly in the market,"},{"time":900000,"text":"and actually makes more money for automakers as well."},{"time":903000,"text":"I'd like to deal with the lack of affordable personal mobility in this country"},{"time":908000,"text":"by making it very cheaply possible for low-income families"},{"time":912000,"text":"to get efficient, reliable, warranted new cars"},{"time":916000,"text":"that they could otherwise never get."},{"time":918000,"text":"And for each car so financed, scrap almost one clunker,"},{"time":922000,"text":"preferably the dirtiest ones."},{"time":924000,"text":"This creates a new million-car-a-year market for Detroit"},{"time":928000,"text":"from customers they weren't going to get otherwise,"},{"time":930000,"text":"because they weren't creditworthy and could never afford a new car."},{"time":933000,"text":"And Detroit will make money on every unit."},{"time":935000,"text":"It turns out that if, say, African-American and white households"},{"time":938000,"text":"had the same car ownership,"},{"time":940000,"text":"it would cut employment disparity about in half"},{"time":944000,"text":"by providing better access to job opportunities."},{"time":946000,"text":"So this is a huge social win, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":948000,"text":"Governments buy hundreds of thousands of cars a year."},{"time":951000,"text":"There are smart ways to buy them and to aggregate that purchasing power"},{"time":955000,"text":"to bring very efficient vehicles into the market faster."},{"time":958000,"text":"And we could even do an X Prize-style golden carrot"},{"time":961000,"text":"that's worth stretching further for."},{"time":963000,"text":"For example, a billion-dollar prize for the first U.S. automaker"},{"time":967000,"text":"to sell 200,000 really advanced vehicles, like some you saw earlier."},{"time":972000,"text":"Then the legacy airlines can't afford to buy the efficient new planes"},{"time":977000,"text":"they desperately need to cut their fuel bills,"},{"time":980000,"text":"but if you felt philosophically you wanted to do anything about that,"},{"time":983000,"text":"there are ways to finance it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"And at the same time to scrap inefficient old planes,"},{"time":989000,"text":"so that if they were otherwise to come back in the air,"},{"time":992000,"text":"they would waste more oil,"},{"time":994000,"text":"and block the uptake of efficient, new planes."},{"time":997000,"text":"Those part inefficient planes"},{"time":999000,"text":"are worth more to society dead than alive."},{"time":1001000,"text":"We ought to take them out back and shoot them,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"and put bounty hunters after them."},{"time":1005000,"text":"Then there's an important military role."},{"time":1008000,"text":"That in creating the move to high-volume,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"low-cost commercial production of these kinds of materials,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"or for that matter, ultra-light steels"},{"time":1017000,"text":"that are a good backup technology,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"the military can do the trick it did"},{"time":1023000,"text":"in turning DARPAnet into the Internet."},{"time":1025000,"text":"Just turn it over to the private sector, and we have an Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"The same for GPS."},{"time":1032000,"text":"The same for the modern semi-conductor industry."},{"time":1034000,"text":"That is, military science and technology that they need"},{"time":1038000,"text":"can create the advanced materials-industrial cluster"},{"time":1041000,"text":"that transforms its civilian economy and gets the country off oil,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"which would be a huge contribution to eliminating conflict over oil"},{"time":1047000,"text":"and advancing national and global security."},{"time":1049000,"text":"Then we need to retool the car industry and do retraining,"},{"time":1054000,"text":"and shift the convergence of the energy and ag-value chains"},{"time":1058000,"text":"to shift faster from hydrocarbons to carbohydrates,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"and get out of our own way in other ways."},{"time":1063000,"text":"And make the transition to more efficient vehicles go faster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068000,"text":"But here's how the whole thing fits together."},{"time":1070000,"text":"Instead of official forecasts of oil use"},{"time":1073000,"text":"and oil imports going forever up,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"they can turn down with the 12 dollars a barrel efficiency,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"down steeply by adding the supply-side substitutions at 18 bucks,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"all implemented at slower rates than we've done before when we paid attention."},{"time":1087000,"text":"And if we start adding tranches of hydrogen in there,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"we are rapidly off imports and completely off oil in the 2040s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1094000,"text":"And the one thing I'd like to point out here is that we've done this before."},{"time":1098000,"text":"In this eight-year period, 1977 to 85, when we last paid attention,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"the economy grew 27 percent, oil use fell 17 percent,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"oil imports fell 50 percent, oil imports from the Persian Gulf fell 87 percent."},{"time":1113000,"text":"They would have been gone if we'd kept that up one more year."},{"time":1116000,"text":"Well, that was with very old technologies and delivery methods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1120000,"text":"We could rerun that play a lot better now."},{"time":1123000,"text":"And yet what we proved then is the U.S. has more market power than OPEC."},{"time":1126000,"text":"Ours is on the demand side."},{"time":1128000,"text":"We are the Saudi Arabia of \"nega-barrels.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":1130000,"text":"We can use less oil faster than they can conveniently sell less oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1135000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1142000,"text":"Whatever your reason for wanting to do this,"},{"time":1145000,"text":"whether you're concerned about national security or price volatility --"},{"time":1148000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1149000,"text":"-- or jobs, or the planet, or your grand-kids,"},{"time":1152000,"text":"it seems to me that this is an oil endgame"},{"time":1155000,"text":"that we should all be playing to win."},{"time":1157000,"text":"Please download your copy, and thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1160000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}